# HPC & execution (Alioth / lustre)

## Executor

- Production: `-profile <panel>,alioth_slurm,singularity` (e.g. `early,alioth_slurm,singularity`)
- Local/dev: `alioth_local` or `dev` with same Singularity bind: `-B /lustre1,/lustre2`
- Grid search batch: `-profile grid_search,singularity` + `run_grid_search.sh` loops thresholds into separate `--outdir`

## Containers (`conf/alioth_slurm.config`)

| Process pattern | Image |
|-----------------|--------|
| `METHYLDACKEL.*` | `containers/methyldackel.sif` |
| `PICARD_*` | `containers/picard_3.4.0.sif` |
| Most local/python | `containers/common_tools.sif` |

- Default queue: `cn-long`; `publishDir` → `${params.outdir}/<process_name>/`
- Intermediate steps often `publishDir = [ enabled: false ]`

## Required launch args

```bash
nextflow run main.nf \
  --input <samplesheet.csv> \
  --outdir <lustre_results_path> \
  --step <split_bam|beta_zscore|grid_search>
```

Panel profile supplies `--fasta`, `--cpg_list`, `--snp_list`, `--reference_beta_zscore_matrix`, thresholds.

## Agent notes

- Do not commit `.sif` files; paths use `${baseDir}/containers/...`
- Changing cpus/memory/time requires matching process names in config `withName:` blocks
- `workDir` is shared on lustre — warn user before suggesting concurrent runs with same workDir
